text:
The Kitzbühel District is a district in Tyrol, Austria. It borders Bavaria (Germany) in the north, the Kufstein and Schwaz districts in the west, and the Pinzgau region (Salzburg) in the east and south.
It has an area of 1,163.06 km². As of 2012, 61,966 people lived there. The administrative center of the district is Kitzbühel.
Places.
The district has 20 municipalities, one of them is a town, and three of them are market towns.
